This document outlines the recommended file structure for a modern Next.js application using TypeScript, shadcn/ui components, and Tailwind CSS. Each section includes context descriptions to help Cursor understand the purpose of different files and directories.

## Root Directory Structure

/
├── .github/                    # GitHub-specific configuration for CI/CD workflows
├── .husky/                     # Git hooks for enforcing code quality before commits
├── .vscode/                    # VSCode-specific settings for consistent developer experience
├── app/                        # Next.js App Router directory containing routes and layouts
├── components/                 # Reusable UI components for the application
├── config/                     # Configuration files for the application
├── hooks/                      # Custom React hooks for shared functionality
├── lib/                        # Utility functions and shared code
├── providers/                  # React context providers for global state management
├── public/                     # Static assets served directly by Next.js
├── scripts/                    # Utility scripts for development and deployment
├── styles/                     # Global styles and Tailwind configuration
├── types/                      # TypeScript type definitions and interfaces
├── .env.example                # Example environment variables file
├── .eslintrc.json             # ESLint configuration for code quality
├── .gitignore                  # Specifies files to be ignored by Git
├── .prettierrc                 # Prettier configuration for code formatting
├── components.json            # shadcn/ui component configuration
├── next.config.js             # Next.js configuration
├── package.json               # Project dependencies and scripts
├── postcss.config.js          # PostCSS configuration for Tailwind
├── README.md                  # Project documentation
├── tailwind.config.js         # Tailwind CSS configuration
└── tsconfig.json              # TypeScript configuration